citations:
    citation-adwd-the-discarded-knight:
        source: source-adwd
        properties:
            locator: "The Discarded Knight"
            text_from_source: "Prince Quentyn was listening intently, at least. That one is his father's son. Short and stocky, plain-faced, he seemed a decent lad, sober, sensible, dutiful … but not the sort to make a young girl's heart beat faster."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Barristan Selmy POV. Hizdahr zo Loraq holds court as King of Meereen. Yunkish delegation led by three Wise Masters delivers the severed head of Admiral Groleo — executed as reprisal for the death of Yurkhaz zo Yunzak at Daznak's Pit. Sellsword captain Bloodbeard present. Three Meereenese hostages returned. Quentyn Martell attends court with Gerris Drinkwater and Archibald Yronwood. Barristan warns Quentyn to leave Meereen. He describes the poisoned locusts at Daznak's Pit and warns Quentyn could be blamed. Goghor the Giant, the Spotted Cat, Khrazz, and Belaquo Bone-breaker serve as Hizdahr's pit-fighter guards. Marghaz zo Loraq now commands the Brazen Beasts."
